&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;34 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a motivated Clinical Sister to complement our welcoming multi-disciplinary team within the Eye Outpatients and Eye Casualty Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Department of Ophthalmology at James Cook University Hospital is looking to recruit a highly motivated Clinical Sister to join our Eye casualty Team based in eye outpatients department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to work in a professional and friendly atmosphere with people that are dedicated to providing first class care to ophthalmic casualties?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work autonomously in this progressive role triaging patients seeing treating and discharging patients using strict nursing competencies in an acute setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a great opportunity to join our team and to be involved in the future of Ophthalmology care here at James Cook.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Carol O’Connor (Ophthalmology Manager)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel: 01642 850850 ext.54041&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
